# scripts/register-with-store.mjs loads env files in this order (first non-
# empty value per variable wins; real shell env always beats files):
#
#   1. shell env       — `WEBFACTORY_STORE_API_KEY=... node ...`
#   2. ~/WebFactory/.env.local         — local override (gitignored)
#   3. ~/WebFactory/.env               — committed-defaults fallback (gitignored)
#   4. ~/webfactory-store/.env.local   — sibling project's env file
#
# Tier 4 is the easiest path for the current single shared secret
# (WEBFACTORY_STORE_API_KEY): the storefront repo already has it via
# `vercel env pull`, and WebFactory reads it from there directly. NO COPY/
# PASTE BETWEEN REPOS NEEDED. Rotating the secret in the storefront's env
# automatically picks up here on the next pipeline run.
#
# When you DO want a WebFactory-only override (testing against a preview
# storefront, switching to a non-default intake URL, etc.), copy this file
# to .env.local and fill in only the lines you want to override. Lead-funnel
# scripts use lead-funnel/.env.example for their own subdirectory env.

# WebFactory Store API token (required for Stage 10c — storefront registration).
# Same secret token used by the webfactory-store project at tomekgroup.com to
# authenticate intake POSTs. Set in Vercel production under team_4Hr5Lqd6pY5D7gmeXDVsDmYx.
#
# IF you have ~/webfactory-store cloned locally with `vercel env pull` already
# run, you do NOT need to set this here — register-with-store.mjs reads it
# from the sibling .env.local automatically. Leave it blank or omit it.
#
# If unset across all 4 tiers, Stage 10c soft-fails (logs to
# jobs/{domain}/feedback.md, prints a curl-equivalent for manual retry,
# exits 0 — pipeline does NOT fail).
WEBFACTORY_STORE_API_KEY=

# Optional override — point register-with-store.mjs at a non-production intake
# endpoint (e.g., for testing against a preview deployment of webfactory-store).
# Defaults to https://tomekgroup.com/wf/api/jobs/intake when unset.
# WEBFACTORY_STORE_INTAKE_URL=
